<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-2186] if ftp endpoint is not writeable, the only messages you get are logged at DEBUG level.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-2186</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Using the same project attached to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-2165&quot; title=&quot;ftp uploads can fail: File operation failed:  Connection closed without indication.. Code: 421&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CAMEL-2165&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CAMEL-2165&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, you can delete the &quot;ftp_home&quot; directory, or simply edit user.properties to make the ftp account readonly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While every single write to the camel ftp endpoint will then fail, the only notification of this is at DEBUG level.  In my opinion this should be at least WARN&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12486804">CAMEL-2186</key>
            <summary>if ftp endpoint is not writeable, the only messages you get are logged at DEBUG level.</summary>
