                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12951106" author="karlp" created="Tue, 17 Nov 2009 16:51:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;tested with 2.1-SNAPSHOT as well, dated: 20091117163007&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12953474" author="davsclaus" created="Tue, 17 Nov 2009 17:31:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The failed to write exception should be set on the Exchange so if you have any error handling configured you can take core of it there.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The producers etc should not double log the problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12953498" author="karlp" created="Tue, 17 Nov 2009 17:43:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ok, I&apos;ll agree that the producers shouldn&apos;t.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Perhaps we can relabel this ticket.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I believe that the DefaultErrorHandler should log at INFO at least. I agree it shouldn&apos;t do anything like retries or redeliveries, and I agree that when you&apos;ve got things setup, you&apos;ll have more specific error handling, but currently, without debug level logging, there&apos;s simply no notification at all that anything even went wrong. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12953485" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 18 Nov 2009 08:09:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The issue is you route uses a consumer which just ignores any exceptions since you start a route with a timer.&lt;br/&gt;
When the Exchange is done and it has an exception the timer will just ignore it as it cannot handle exceptions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It aught to log the exception at ERROR level in this name&lt;br/&gt;
org.apache.camel.component.timer&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12953496" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 18 Nov 2009 08:36:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I will improve the TimerConsumer so it will log exchanges that have failed by default at ERROR level. Then you can see this in the log&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12953495" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 18 Nov 2009 08:47:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;trunk: 881699&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12953484" author="karlp" created="Wed, 18 Nov 2009 10:02:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Same affects seda and direct.... &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; And probably other places too.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I really think this belongs in the default error handler &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12956239" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 3 Jun 2010 07:25:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing old resolved issues&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
